HEADWORD: Faradic
<hw>Far*ad"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
Michael <etsep>Faraday</etsep>, the distinguished electrician; --
applied especially to induced currents of electricity, as produced by
certain forms of inductive apparatus, on account of Faraday's
investigations of their laws.</def></p>

<p><ent>Faradization</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Faradism</ent>⟦br⟧
